<p>Your X (Twitter) strategy directly affects your Grok search visibility. Here is the specific optimization checklist.</p>
<h3>Profile Optimization</h3>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Use your brand name as your X handle (consistency with your domain helps entity matching)</li>
<li>[ ] Write a bio that includes your primary keywords and service description</li>
<li>[ ] Pin a post that summarizes what your brand does (Grok reads pinned posts)</li>
<li>[ ] Add your website URL in the profile (creates an explicit entity link)</li>
<li>[ ] Verify your account through X Premium (higher signal weight)</li>
</ul>
<h3>Posting Strategy</h3>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Post 3 to 5 times per week with industry-relevant content</li>
<li>[ ] Use 2 to 3 specific, relevant hashtags per post (not generic trending tags)</li>
<li>[ ] Publish X threads that break down topics in detail (threads generate more engagement)</li>
<li>[ ] Share your blog content with key takeaways (creates X-to-web entity connections)</li>
<li>[ ] Reply to industry discussions (engagement from credible accounts boosts your authority)</li>
<li>[ ] Use @mentions when referencing brands, tools, or people (creates entity relationships)</li>
</ul>
