<h2>How to Optimize Your Website for Grok Citations</h2>
<p>Your website content matters for Grok too. Web optimization for Grok follows the same principles as <a href="/blog/generative-engine-optimization-guide/">generative engine optimization</a> with 2 Grok-specific additions.</p>
<h3>Grok-Specific: Bing Indexation Speed</h3>
<p>Grok uses Bing for web search. If your pages are not indexed in Bing, Grok cannot find them through web search. Most SEOs focus exclusively on Google and neglect Bing indexation.</p>
<p><strong>Action items:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Set up Bing Webmaster Tools and submit your sitemap</li>
<li>[ ] Implement the IndexNow protocol for instant Bing indexation</li>
<li>[ ] Verify your pages appear in Bing search results within 24 hours of publishing</li>
<li>[ ] Check that your <code>robots.txt</code> does not block Bingbot</li>
</ul>
<h3>Grok-Specific: Content Freshness</h3>
<p>Grok weights content freshness more heavily than any other AI platform. A page published and indexed today can appear in Grok answers tomorrow. A page not updated since 2023 gets deprioritized even if the content is accurate.</p>
<p><strong>Action items:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Update high-value pages with current data at least quarterly</li>
<li>[ ] Add "Updated [Month Year]" timestamps that Grok can parse</li>
<li>[ ] Publish new content weekly to maintain a fresh content profile</li>
<li>[ ] Remove or redirect outdated content that contradicts current information</li>
</ul>
